default&#xa0;defaultThe role of the Commissioner in budget and precept settingdefault&#xa0;default13)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn the current economic climate, a primary consideration for all Police and Crime Commissioners is how to balance the books against a backdrop of reducing financial resources, whilst seeking to maintain and improve services to the public.
default&#xa0;default14)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn setting the budget for 2013/14, I had a shortfall of £8m compared to the budget for the previous year.  I proposed to raise the council tax precept by 1.99% to £153
default for a Band D property
default, for the year 2013/14 and following extensive consultation this was supported by over 80% of the public surveyed. 
defaultThe public saw t
defaulthis increase of £3
default per annum
default, or 6p per week, as a small price to pay
default to maintain policing services in Cheshire
default.
default 
default This rise in precept was supported by the Police and Crime Panel and raised £1.2 million to help meet the shortfall.  
default&#xa0;
default15)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI am now in the process of considering the budget options for 2014/15.  A revised medium term financial strategy for 2014-18 has recently been approved and, following the root and branch review, I am confident Cheshire is on track to meet the required savings over this period.  Consultation has been taking place with the public and people have been asked whether they would be happy to pay another increase in the policing pa
defaultrt of the council tax. Out of 1084
default responses to date, 
default7
default5
default%
default of people said they would be prepared to pay a similar increase to last year. However, I am aware that people across the board are struggling, as the economy comes out of the recession. Taking all the above into consideration, I
default a
defaultm minded not to increase the council tax precept for policing next year. 
