defaultA key role of Police and Crime Commissioners is to consult the public on their local priorities for policing to inform the objectives
default contained 
defaultwithin the Police and Crime Plan.  During my election campaign, I listened extensively to the views of the public and took this into account when developing my first Police and Crime Plan.  I am committed to ongoing consultation with the public and recently launched a ‘Victim
default’
defaults Voice’ campaign to find what victims experience and what they expect from the police, victim support organisations and the criminal justice system
default.
default 
defaultThis will 
defaultinform my decisions when I become responsible for commissioning some elements of victims services next year.  My office has also held focus groups with 
defaultmany different victims of crime
default to understand their views on policing including: survivors of domestic abuse
default, people with mental health needs and people from the lesbian, gay, bi-sexual and transgender communities and faith groups.
