default20)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI am a member of the Strategic Police Procurement Board which is working to drive greater collaboration and efficiencies from police procurement practices.  I have also recently met representatives from the Fire &amp; Rescue Service and Ambulance Service to discuss collaboration opportunities between the three services.  Initial discussions have been positive and I am keen that we work together to deliver savings from better joined up working which can be reinvested on the front line.
default&#xa0;
defaultTransparency of and reporting by Commissioners to datedefault&#xa0;default21)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn order to be accountable to the public, the decisions and performance of Commissioners must be visible and transparent.  I have strived to ensure that I am open and to demonstrate a high level of transparency.  Since taking up office, agenda papers for Decision Meetings and the notes of these meetings have been published on my website, providing details of significant decisions which have been taken.  Registers of interests and expense claims for myself and the 
defaultDeputy Commissioner are also readily available on the website.   The Office of the Police and Crime Commissioner for Cheshire is able to demonstrate a high level of compliance with the statutory requirements to publish specified information.  
